LOL LOL LOL <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaidden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidden</A> at: 2/9/01 10:19:56 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/01 8:55:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendside.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think we need to make stuff clear. </span><hr size=1> Well it's a new day, and I'm back with more opinions.<br>
<br>
Frankly the new proposal does not impress me.  It's more of the same from the last proposal, with the added bonus of &quot;as least as effective as jolt&quot;. *dodges wrench*<br>
<br>
Please explain to me how this new proposal is going to save the 5 to 6 rogues which are normally on our raids from dying 1st? Nothing has been done about the problem of rogues trading off aggro to each other.  500 hate is NOTHING ( I will repeat... NOTHING ) in the realm of rogue aggro with how fast we build it up. <br>
<br>
The inherent flaw in all your proposals is this: rogues cannot evade and be put anywhere near the top 6 to 8 spots. If they do, their hate returns to it's previous #1 standing too fast.  Top on the list = dead rogue.  Once again, I am coming from a high level raid perspective, not a level 40 xp party.... which in my opinion is most important because, isn't that what most people are working towards? Level progression... loot progression... challenge progression. You HAVE to tailor evade to the high level player, otherwise there is no incentive to play a rogue other than for casual roleplaying purposes... which is perfectly fine, but that isn't what most rogues out there are looking for.<br>
<br>
VI made a game with no end.  There is no light at the end of the tunnel.  No ultimate goal to strive for... because more will just be created.  Players continue their characters because they hope that each new level, and each new month, will bring greater challenge and greater enjoyment.  I know we all have different perspectives on rogues... and we're all different levels, but character progression is a goal of every player.  Whether it's your reputation and friends, your level, or your loot.. everyone strives to enchance their character.  We wouldn't be playing if it were otherwise.  <br>
<br>
Evade plays a major role in this progression of goals... it provides rogues with a NECESSARY tool for dealing with the damage capability YOU (VI) gave us.  Without out, we have no purpose on high level raids, and it takes away any incentive of being (or striving to be) a high level rogue. If the real problem here is class balance in relation to how much damage rogues do vs. other classes, then directly fix it be done with so the high level rogue population can mass exodus away from EQ (or start a new char).  <br>
<br>
Lets stop arguing about evade... the high level population input is not being taken into consideration.  Evade IS GOING to be nerfed into oblivion from it's current form. Lets all take a deep breath and just accept that.  Instead lets discuss about why evade was nerfed to begin with... shall we? <br>
<br>
VI obviously knew coming into this rogue talk that evade was going to change.  Absor told us that before we started (and as uninformed as he was about the rogue class or their skills he still knew that the uppers at VI wanted it nerfed).  Why? Is it too powerful? Is rogue damage being realigned with other tank classes? Maybe too many wizards have been making rogues lately because they felt useless? (boy they are gonna be pissed now that they have to start over again).  <br>
<br>
Rogues have one purpose... and I know some ppl disagree with this... but it's damage. Lots of it. Forget CR... forget pulling... forget tanking...we are substandard in all those capacities to at least 1 other class.  We paid a high price for being the best at damage before the 1st evade skill was implemented. Death. Lack of groups. General sentiment as the worst class in EQ.  Many rogues quit... heck even I did for a few months.  Then evade came and saved us.... and the rogue community rejoiced.  Slowly, as rogue skills were increased in RoK, and as lower delay/higher damage weapons started coming out, rogues emerged as the clear choice for melee damage.  There was only 1 reason... and 1 reason alone why this happened. Evade (yep, short revisit to this argument).  Without evade in it's current form (or some compromised form that Icebreaker proposed and I have supported), we become substandard in the damage department as well.  I don't care if you throw numbers at me until you are blue in the face, I am telling you how it's actually going to happen in the game.  Arbitrary hate values... what class is ahead of who on in your example... it's all meaningless.  Rogues will occupy the top spots on the hate list... in longer battles it will be more pronounced (500 hate is a drop in the bucket and I will be evading onto a fellow guild rogue).<br>
<br>
So, we know rogues do the most damage.  We know evade contributes to that.  Nerf evade == nerf rogue damage.  Wasn't that the idea to begin with? I can deal with never reaching the light in the tunnel... but don't drop the roof of the tunnel on our journey through it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 2/8/01 9:02:25 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=anaia>Anaia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/01 8:59:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kendrick my friend...</span><hr size=1> One thing I would like to know is if evade has a 67% chance to work after level 40, does this mean that your actual hide skill percentage has no berring on how successful you are in attempting to evade?  Have I been working my hide skill for no reason thinking all the while that it did? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/01 9:01:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kendrick my friend...</span><hr size=1> Hide skill reaches 200 at level 39. You can't raise it any further.<br>
