Absor first suggested a 33% reduction in hate on a successful evade, and we pointed out why that would not work...<br>
Absor has now suggested a combination of putting you between 2 and 3 if you are number one, dropping you a small percent if you are not, and capping this with a minimum of a jolt, and we pointed out why that would not work...<br>
<br>
HOWEVER!!! The situations where the percentage method fails seems to be covered by the 2/3 method, and vice versa. Why not combine them? Take the more beneficial of the 2 options, and voila, rogues are still accountable for the damage they do, but are not limited to one or two rogues on raids, and at the same time are not limited to a hard cap on how much they can outdamage the main tank by. 33%, and midway between 2/3, those are numbers that can be adjusted and made to work out, but the theory behind this is sound and one I would support.<br>
<br>
I won't stand by any change, though, that would make our damage output appreciably less than it is now. I am willing to use strategy though. If a fight is typically lasting 20 seconds, I'll let the tank get a full combat round in now. If they're lasting a minute, I might give them two combat rounds. That's not a real nerf to damage, maybe 5% at most, and it's really just the rogue using some strategy. But if we have to turn attack off on a regular basis (other than during our evade hotkey), skip backstabs, or join the wizzie on the sidelines, then rogues will be a 'broken', not a 'balanced' class. <p><p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=37752">Darkrok Shadowwalker</a> - Redeemed Dwarven Rogue of 40 Missions, <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Action=Journal&Jid=4546&Id=37752">Merchant Extraordinaire</a><br>
